  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0da7 73\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db6\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dcf \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "73 percent of the required fertilizers have been distributed",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is revealed by the information of Lanka Fertilizer Company Limited that 73% of the requirement of urea fertilizer required for rice cultivation in this year's rice season has been released as of yesterday (23rd).",
        "According to the information, 17119.450 metric tons of urea fertilizer has been allocated for all the districts where rice cultivation is being done and out of which 12563.400 metric tons have been distributed to all the districts. Also, the remaining amount of 4556.050 metric tons of urea fertilizer will be distributed in the future. Said.",
        "Also, Hambantota District Secretary Mr. Priyantha Sumanasekara said that 94% of the urea fertilizer required for paddy cultivation in the Yala season in Hambantota district has been released so far and accordingly, paddy cultivation has been done on more than 32000 acres of paddy land in all parts of the district.",
        "He further said that there is a possibility to harvest paddy in August and September in the district and arrangements are being made to provide fuel to the farmers for that purpose."
      ],
